ely used, not only in mathematics but also in the natural and social sciences, for studying such subjects as weather problems, traffic flow, electronic circuits, and population genetics. In 1983 Halmos received the coveted Steele Prize for exposition from the American Mathematical Society for "his many graduate texts in mathematics dealing with finite dimensional vector spaces, measure theory, ergodic theory, and Hilbert space."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aLogic, Symbolic and mathematical. 0aMathematical models. 0aVector spaces. 7aMATHEMATICS / Algebra / Linear.2bisacsh  aAbsolute value.  aAccuracy and precision.  aAddition.  aAffine space.  aAlgebraic closure.  aAlgebraic equation.  aAlgebraic operation.  aAlgebraically closed field.  aAssociative property.  aAutomorphism.  aAxiom.  aBanach space.  aBasis (linear algebra).  aBilinear form.  aBounded operator.  aCardinal number.  aCayley transform.  aCharacteristic equation.  aCharacterization (mathematics).  aCoefficient.  aCommutative property.  aComplex number.  aComplex plane.  aComputation.  aCongruence relation.  aConvex set.  aCoordinate system.  aDeterminant.  aDiagonal matrix.  aDimension (vector space).  aDimension.  aDimensional analysis.  aDirect product.  aDirect proof.  aDirect sum.  aDivision by zero.  aDot product.  aDual basis.  aEigenvalues and eigenvectors.  aElementary proof.  aEquation.  aEuclidean space.  aExistential quantification.  aFunction of a real variable.  aFunctional calculus.  aFundamental theorem.  aGeometry.  aGram–Schmidt process.  aHermitian matrix.  aHilbert space.  aInfimum and supremum.  aJordan normal form.  aLebesgue integration.  aLinear combination.  aLinear function.  aLinear independence.  aLinear map.